sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Kuadrant/Authorino<br/>Gateway Auth
    participant API as Apiserver<br/>8000/TCP
    participant PG as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Redis as Redis/Valkey<br/>6379/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP
    participant Proc as Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant Inf as llm-d Router<br/>Inference Gateway
    participant GC as GC<br/>9091/TCP

    Note over Client,GC: Flow 1: Batch Job Submission

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/files (multipart/form-data)<br/>Auth: API key / SA token
    GW->>API: Validated request<br/>X-MaaS-Username: tenant-id
    API->>S3: PutObject (input file)<br/>HTTPS / AWS IAM
    API->>PG: INSERT file record<br/>pgx / Connection URL
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {file_id}

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches<br/>Auth: API key / SA token
    GW->>API: Validated request
    API->>PG: INSERT batch record<br/>pgx / Connection URL
    API->>Redis: ZADD priority queue<br/>RESP / Connection URL
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {batch_id, status: validating}

    Note over Client,GC: Flow 2: Batch Job Processing

    loop Poll queue (every 5s)
        Proc->>Redis: BZMPOP (blocking dequeue)<br/>RESP / Connection URL
    end
    Proc->>PG: SELECT batch details<br/>pgx
    Proc->>S3: GetObject (input file)<br/>HTTPS / AWS IAM
    Note over Proc: Build per-model execution plan<br/>AIMD concurrency control

    loop For each request in batch (up to 50,000)
        Proc->>Inf: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS / API key or mTLS
        Inf-->>Proc: 200 OK (inference result)
        Note over Proc: AIMD: additive increase on success
        alt 429 Too Many Requests or 5xx
            Inf-->>Proc: 429/5xx error
            Note over Proc: AIMD: multiplicative decrease<br/>(backoff_factor: 0.5)
        end
    end

    Proc->>S3: PutObject (output file)<br/>HTTPS / AWS IAM
    Proc->>PG: UPDATE batch status=completed<br/>pgx / CAS update
    Proc->>Redis: SET status, cleanup inflight<br/>RESP

    Note over Client,GC: Flow 3: Job Cancellation

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Auth: API key / SA token
    GW->>API: Validated request
    API->>PG: UPDATE batch status=cancelling<br/>pgx / CAS update
    API->>Redis: RPUSH cancel event<br/>RESP
    API-->>Client: 200 OK {status: cancelling}
    Redis-->>Proc: BLMPOP cancel event
    Note over Proc: Stop dispatching,<br/>write partial results
    Proc->>S3: PutObject (partial output)<br/>HTTPS
    Proc->>PG: UPDATE status=cancelled<br/>pgx

    Note over Client,GC: Flow 4: Garbage Collection

    loop Every 1h (configurable)
        GC->>PG: SELECT expired batches/files<br/>pgx
        GC->>S3: DeleteObject (expired files)<br/>HTTPS / AWS IAM
        GC->>PG: DELETE expired records<br/>pgx
    end

    Note over GC,Redis: Orphan Reconciliation (every 60m)
    GC->>Redis: HGETALL inflight hash<br/>RESP
    GC->>PG: Cross-reference with DB
    Note over GC: Re-enqueue or finalize<br/>orphaned jobs
